div.div: Update README.md to enhance project documentation and detail visualization improvements
Removes CSS reference from YAML header for tufte_html output

Adds loading of instructional staff data from CSV
Implements functionality to load instructional staff data from a CSV file, enhancing data accessibility for further analysis.
This addition supports the creation of plots by providing the necessary data directly from the specified file location.

Adds data transformation for staff dataset
Transforms the staff data from wide to long format, ensuring that the `year` column is converted from character to numeric for accurate plotting.
Utilizes the pipe operator for smoother operation chaining and retains `faculty_type` during the transformation.

Adds initial line plot without grouping by faculty type
Introduces a line plot visualization of staff data, coloring lines by faculty type.
This enhancement allows for better visual analysis of trends over the years.

Adds initial visualization analysis for staff data
Introduces an analysis section to highlight issues in the initial staff data visualization, including disconnected lines due to missing aesthetics and suboptimal default settings for communication.
Improves clarity on the visual representation challenges faced in the dataset.

Improves fisheries data visualization for clarity and accessibility
Enhances the final visualization by implementing a horizontal bar orientation for better readability of country names and sorting bars by total production for easier comparison.
Converts units to million tonnes, adds clear titles and labels, utilizes a colorblind-friendly palette, and moves the legend for better space utilization.
Technical adjustments include optimized bar width, removal of unnecessary gridlines, increased font sizes, and reversed stacking order to promote intuitive reading and efficient use of space.
These design choices ensure a clear hierarchy of information and enhance accessibility.

Improves fisheries visualization with enhanced readability
Enhances the fisheries production plot by implementing stacked bars with a reversed stacking order, utilizing a colorblind-friendly palette, and adding clear titles and labels.
Adopts a minimal theme with an increased base font size for better visibility and adjusts x-axis expansion for improved spacing of data points.

Improves fisheries data transformation for visualization
Enhances data processing by calculating total production from capture and aquaculture, reordering countries by total, and converting the dataset to long format for a stacked bar plot.
This transformation ensures better readability and prepares the data structure for effective visualization.
Improves overall clarity and organization in fisheries data analysis.

Enhances visualization and storytelling elements in plot
Implements advanced techniques to improve visual clarity and engagement in the plot.
- Emphasizes part-time faculty trends with thicker lines and contrasting colors, while de-emphasizing other trends. - Adds data points for the start and end years, and percentage labels for 2011 for better information delivery. - Removes the legend for a cleaner look, as color coding is intuitive. - Sets y-axis limits and increases figure dimensions for improved readability. - Introduces clear titles and subtitles to guide the viewerâ€™s attention and provide essential statistics.
These changes aim to enhance the interpretability and appeal of the visual presentation.
Improves plot clarity and storytelling elements
Enhances visualization techniques for better interpretability and engagement.
- Emphasizes part-time faculty trends with thicker lines and contrasting colors. - Adds data points and percentage labels for clearer information delivery. - Removes the legend for a cleaner appearance, relying on intuitive color coding. - Adjusts y-axis limits and increases figure size for improved readability. - Introduces clear titles and subtitles to guide viewer attention and highlight key statistics.

Improves visualization of part-time faculty trends
Enhances the plot by adding refined visual elements to better highlight part-time faculty trends.
Includes distinct line sizes and colors for clarity, adds data points for start and end years, and incorporates percentage labels for better data representation.

Improves plot visualization and adds necessary commentary
Adds comments highlighting issues with the initial plot, including disconnected lines due to missing grouping, suboptimal aesthetics, and lack of titles and labels.
Addresses the warning about insufficient data for each faculty type year combination, emphasizing the need for better visualization practices.

Refactors data transformation for time series visualization
Implements the use of the pipe operator for chaining operations, reshaping the dataset from wide to long format while retaining `faculty_type` and creating numeric `year` and `value` columns.
This transformation enhances the ability to create time series visualizations with ggplot2 by ensuring proper data formatting.

Adds improved visualization for global fisheries production
Enhances the readability of the fisheries data visualization by implementing a stacked bar chart.
The updated plot features a clear title and subtitle, improved labeling, and a refined theme for better presentation.
This change aims to facilitate understanding of global fisheries production by country in 2016.

Adds data transformation for improved fisheries visualization
Transforms fisheries data to calculate totals and enhance readability.
Implements a new data structure that reorders countries based on total capture and aquaculture tonnage.
This change aims to improve the clarity and effectiveness of the fisheries visualization.

Improves fisheries visualization for enhanced readability
Enhances the fisheries visualization by implementing several improvements:
- Uses horizontal bars for better readability of country names - Sorts countries by total production - Clarifies units to million tonnes - Adds proper labels and legend - Introduces a better color scheme
These changes aim to improve the overall readability and effectiveness of the visualization.

Removes eval=FALSE from data loading chunk
Eliminates the eval=FALSE option in the data loading chunk to ensure the fisheries data is loaded during the document execution.
This change enhances the functionality by allowing the code to run as intended, making the data accessible for subsequent analysis.

Adds improved plot visualization for faculty data
Enhances the existing plot by introducing a more accessible color scheme and adding data labels for clarity.
The updated visualization highlights the rise of part-time faculty in higher education from 1975 to 2011, making it easier to interpret trends and comparisons.
Improves overall presentation and readability of the data.

Improves plot clarity and accessibility
Enhances the original plot by highlighting the part-time faculty trend, adding a more informative title and subtitle, using an accessible color scheme, and including data labels at the start and end points.
These changes aim to effectively convey the rising proportion of part-time faculty over time.

Adds line plot for trends in instructional staff employment
Implements a line plot to visualize trends in instructional staff employment status from 1975 to 2011.
Enhances the plot with improved titles, axis labels, and a legend for clarity.
The changes aim to effectively illustrate the rising proportion of part-time faculty over time compared to other faculty types.

Enhances line plot aesthetics and adds labels
Improves the visual presentation of the instructional staff employment status plot by increasing line thickness, adding a title, subtitle, and axis labels.
Applies a minimal theme, a color palette, and adjusts the legend position for better clarity and visual appeal.

Adds initial HTML structure and styling for Lab 05
Introduces a new HTML file that establishes the layout and design for Lab 05.
Implements responsive styling and custom fonts to enhance readability and presentation.
Includes a script to ensure compatibility with specific Pandoc versions by removing attributes from headers.
No issues are addressed, but the changes enhance the overall user experience.

Adds new PDF figures for data wrangling analysis
Introduces four new PDF files to support data visualization in the analysis process.
These figures will enhance the clarity of the results and aid in the interpretation of the data.

Adds analysis of minimum distances for states
Introduces R code to compare the mean and median of minimum distances between Denny's and La Quinta locations for several states.
Highlights the state with the smallest distance, which supports the reasoning behind Mitch Hedberg's joke.
Encourages reviewing and finalizing the document for submission.

Adds analysis for Florida state distances
Introduces a new section to analyze the distribution of distances between Denny's and La Quinta locations in Florida.
This change enables users to explore patterns similar to those observed in Texas, enhancing the comparative analysis across different states.

Adds analysis of closest distances for Texas locations
Implements distance analysis for Denny's and La Quinta locations in Texas, revealing shorter distances compared to previous states analyzed.
The addition includes data filtering, distance calculation, and visualization through a histogram, supporting the observation of closer paired establishments in Texas.
Highlights patterns relevant to Mitch Hedberg's joke about proximity of locations.

Adds analysis and visualization of Denny's and La Quinta in NC
Implements data filtering, joining, and distance calculation for Denny's and La Quinta locations in North Carolina.
Introduces a histogram to visualize the distribution of the shortest distances between paired locations, highlighting geographic trends in NC compared to Alaska.
Enhances the analysis framework by expanding to NC, offering insights into location density and distance metrics.

Adds analysis and visualization of closest Denny's distances
Introduces summary statistics and a histogram visualization for the distances between Denny's and the nearest La Quinta locations in Alaska.
This enhancement provides insights into the geographic distribution of these distances, highlighting the impact of Alaska's geography on proximity.
Improves overall data analysis capabilities for the project.

Enables evaluation of minimum distance calculation
Removes the `eval = FALSE` flag to allow execution of the R code chunk that calculates the minimum distance between Denny's and La Quinta locations.
This change improves the functionality by ensuring that the distance calculation is performed when the document is run, providing users with the necessary insights without manual intervention.

Adds Haversine distance calculation to data frame
Introduces a new column 'distance' to calculate the Haversine distance in kilometers between each Denny's and La Quinta location.
This enhancement allows for better spatial analysis of the locations, facilitating subsequent calculations of minimum distances.

Adds example usage for `mutate()` function
Clarifies the use of the `mutate()` function from the tidyverse by providing an example in the documentation.
This improves understanding for users on how to add new variables to a data frame while retaining existing ones.

Adds observation count and variable names for joined data
Implements code to display the number of observations and variable names in the joined data frame.
Clarifies the significance of suffixes `.x` and `.y` in variable names to indicate their origin from the original data frames, addressing potential confusion with duplicate names.

Adds calculation for pairings between Denny's and La Quinta
Introduces a calculation to determine the total pairings between Denny's and La Quinta locations in Alaska.
This change enhances the analysis by providing a clear numerical basis for the number of distance calculations needed, facilitating further data processing.

Adds note about La Quinta locations in Alaska
Includes a remark indicating that there are 2 La Quinta locations in Alaska, enhancing the clarity of the dataset for further analysis.
This addition assists in understanding the geographical context before calculating distances between Denny's and La Quinta locations.

Adds author information to the document header
Includes the author's name, Tina Huynh, in the document header for improved attribution.
This change enhances the clarity of authorship in the lab report.
Initialize README.md with Nobel laureates analysis overview and dataset details
Update lab-03-nobel-laureates.tex with author name, data analysis, and visualizations; add insights on immigrant Nobel laureates.
Add new PDF figures for faceted and stacked bar plots in the Nobel laureates analysis
Add analysis for immigrant Nobel laureates winning in the US
Add stacked bar plot visualization for Nobel laureates by award country and birth country
Add calculation for count of Nobel laureates born in the US
Add faceted bar plot visualization for Nobel laureates by category and country
Rename code chunk for filtering living Nobel laureates to improve clarity
Add inline code to display the number of observations and variables in the dataset
Update author name in YAML header to reflect correct attribution
